values.title: Multilanguage
values.text: Blokkli supports a multilingual workflow. When translating content, the structure can not be altered.

values.title: Integration with Drupal Paragraphs
values.lead: Blokkli comes with an adapter to integrate the editor in existing or new Paragraphs based setups. The "Paragraphs Builder" Drupal module implements all features required to use Blokkli as your editing experience.

values.text:
Edit state entity to keep track of mutations
Plugin system for custom mutations and actions
GraphQL schema extension

values.title: Just the editor
values.lead: Blokkli only requires a simple data structure and integrates with any CMS using a single adapter interface.

values.title: Multilingual Support and Advanced Previewing
values.lead: Blokkli transcends language barriers and offers advanced previewing options, ensuring your content resonates globally.

values.title: Mobile First
values.text: Direct mobile preview from within the editor. Instantly see how changes affect mobile rendering.

values.title: Hands-on Preview
values.text: If supported by the backend, Blokkli can generate a QR code that can be scanned on a smartphone to see and feel a preview of the page, with live reloading.

values.title: Simple
values.text: Blokkli provides an adapter to integrate the editor with any existing Paragraphs based Drupal setup.

values.title: Integrates in any Nuxt setup
values.lead: Blocks are rendered with minimal overhead. Full SSR support, no leaking CSS.

values.title: It's just the editor
values.lead: Blokkli only requires a simple data structure and integrates with any CMS using a single adapter interface.

values.title: Add List
values.text: List to easily drag and drop new blocks

values.title: Artboard
values.text: Pan and zoom pages for easy overview

values.title: Clipboard
values.text: Paste text, images or links to create new blocks

values.title: Comments
values.text: Add comments to one or more blocks and mark comments as resolved.

values.title: Conversions
values.text: Convert one or more blocks to different types while preserving their content.

values.title: Entity Title & Form
values.text: Seamlessly integrate CMS forms to edit non-block content like page title, metatags, etc.

values.title: Grid
values.text: Show a grid overlay in the editor.

values.title: Form
values.text: Integrates forms from a CMS via iframe. Render your own forms directly inside the editor.

values.title: History
values.text: Quickly undo or redo changes or jump to any point in the history stack.

values.title: Import Existing
values.text: Offer a way to import content from existing pages or templates.

values.title: Library
values.text: Make blocks reusable by adding them to a library. Easily drag and drop library blocks into the page.

values.title: Mask
values.text: Hide parts of the page that can't be changed via the editor (header, footer, etc.)

values.title: Multiselect
values.text: Select one or more blocks using a selection rectangle.

values.title: Options
values.text: Implement block options that are rendered directly in the editor, with instant preview.

values.title: Ownership
values.text: Restrict editing to a single person.

values.title: Preview
values.text: Live mobile preview via iframe, separate URL or by scanning a QR code to preview on a smartphone.

values.title: Publish
values.text: Apply changes from the history stack and publish them. Implement custom publishing workflows by extending the feature.

values.title: Search
values.text: Find blocks on the current page. Implement custom providers to search existing content or images. Drag and drop search items to create blocks.

values.title: Settings
values.text: Let users configure the editor. Add custom settings to the form.

values.title: Structure
values.text: Quick overview of the page structure. Click to jump to block.

values.title: Transform
values.text: Implement custom actions to transform one or more blocks, like merging or splitting.

values.title: Translations
values.text: Adds support for multilingual content. Easy switch between enabled languages.

values.title: Validations
values.text: Give hints about validation errors like missing alt texts, empty blocks or excessive use of line breaks.

values.title: Easily find existing content
values.lead: Easily locate content and transform your blocks to suit your needs, adding flexibility to your page design.
